{"key":"post-11977946","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>11977946</id>\n<content>&lt;/font&gt;&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;font class=&quot;small&quot;&gt;Quote:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;hr /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;TuBlynd said:&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br /&gt;1. The water should not be boiling but just producing steam.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;hr /&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;font class=&quot;post&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;That is flat-out wrong.&amp;nbsp; The water should be in a rapid boil, with the jars on a rack above the water.&amp;nbsp; It's the steam that sterilizes the product.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Use a pot with a tight fitting lid.&amp;nbsp; Once steam begins escaping from under the lid, turn down the stove to the minimum setting which will keep a small amount of steam escaping, and at this point you set the timer for 90 minutes, not before.&amp;nbsp; Add water during the process if necessary to prevent the pot from boiling dry.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;To the original poster, use 1/2 pint wide mouth jars, not pints.&amp;nbsp; That isn't the reason you got zero germination, but performance is less with larger jars.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>11978613</next>\n<prev>11977839</prev>\n<first>11965827</first>\n<last>11998437</last>\n<when>1265512110</when>\n<utime>02/07/10 05:08 AM</utime>\n</post>"}